The paper deals with fine-grained visual categorization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves regularizers that guide the extracted features to represent semantic parts and improve the robustness of multi-scale features, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of large datasets like NABirds, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the contributions of different components of the approach and demonstrating state-of-the-art performance, which are common tasks in natural language processing (cs.CL).
